docs.name: Tonnellerie Francois Freres SA (TFF)
docs.description: TFF Group, formerly Tonnellerie Francois Freres SA, is a France-based company that manufactures and distributes oak barrels that are used to conserve and transport liquids. The Company has four core businesses: stave milling, cooperage, cask manufacturing and oak wine-aging products. Tonnellerie Francois Freres SA also offers oak products for oenology, where the wine is put in contact with wood in varied forms, and has developed products for the alcohol maturing and aging market, especially the whisky market. The Company offers four brands of barrels: Exclusif, Privilege, Classique and Horizon. As of December 31, 2011, Tonnellerie Francois Freres SA operated through its subsidiaries, including: Sogibois, Bouyoud, Treuil, Francois Inc, Classic Oak New Zealand, Demptos Napa, among others. The Company has operating units in France, the United States, Spain, Hungary, South Africa, China, New Zealand, Australia and Ireland.

docs.name: Quotium Technologies SA (QTE)
docs.description: Quotium Technologies SA, (formerly known as Icom Informatique), is a France-based company that specializes in the publishing and marketing communication software. The Company offers such solutions as Web application security; Load testing and application performance; Availability and performance of applications in production and Security and durability of data stored on tape. The Company sells its products through the world to Information Technology (IT) departments in different sectors, such as banking, insurance, administration, services, and industry. Quotium Technologies operates its wholly owned subsidiary Quotium Technologies Ltd, based in the United Kingdom. As of December 31, 2011, Technologies SAS held a 100% stake in the Company's shareholdings.

docs.name: Uniontown Energy Inc (UTOG)
docs.description: Uniontown Energy Inc. is an exploration-stage company. The Company is an independent oil and natural gas company engaged in the acquisition and exploration of oil and natural gas properties located within America's borders. Its holdings encompass 43,480 acres. The Company's properties and operations include the Darby Block Property, the New Miami Property, the Musselshell Property and the Teton River Property. On April 5, 2011, the Company entered into an option agreement to purchase a 75% interest in Musselshell Prospect in Montana. On April 8, 2011, the Company entered into an exploration agreement for the acquisition and exploration of a 75% interest in certain oil and gas claims in the area of Pondera County, Montana.

docs.name: FTORX: First Investors Multi State Insured Txfr Fd Or S
docs.description:
The investment seeks a high level of interest income that is exempt from both federal and state income tax for individual residents of the state of Oregon; it also seeks income that is not a tax preference item for purposes of the federal alternative minimum tax.
 The fund attempts to invest all of its assets in municipal securities that pay interest that is exempt from both federal income tax, including the AMT, and any applicable state income tax for individual residents of the state of Oregon. It generally invests only in high quality municipal securities. Typically, the securities purchased have maturities of 15 years or more.

docs.name: Utilico Pref-2014 (UTLB)
docs.description: Historical stock prices for Utilico Pref-2014 (UTLB). Utilico Finance Limited, formerly Utilico Limited, is a Bermuda-based closed-end investment company. The Company's investment objective is to finance and repay the zero dividend preference (ZDP) shares. The Company seeks to finance its ZDP shares debt by lending current asset funds to its Parent Company, Utilico Investments Limited (UIL). Its objective is to maximize shareholder returns by identifying and investing in investments where the underlying value is not reflected in the market price. The Company's portfolio holding portfolio includes Resolute Mining Limited, Utilico Emerging Markets Limited, Infratil Limited, Bermuda Commercial Bank, Jersey Electricity Company Limited, Vix Technology, Renewable Energy Generation Ltd, Keytech Limited, Ascendant Group Limited and Augean

docs.name: RPMGX: T. Rowe Price Mid-Cap Growth Fund Inc.
docs.description:
The investment seeks long-term capital appreciation.
 The fund normally invests at least 80% of net assets (including any borrowings for investment purposes) in a diversified portfolio of common stocks of mid-cap companies whose earnings T. Rowe Price expects to grow at a faster rate than the average company. It defines mid-cap companies as those whose market capitalization falls within the range of either the S&P MidCap 400 Index or the Russell Midcap Growth Index. While most assets will typically be invested in U.S. common stocks, the fund may invest in foreign stocks in keeping with the fund's objectives.

docs.name: Solocal Group SA (LOCAL)
docs.description: Solocal Group, (Pagesjaunes Groupe SA), is a France-based company specialized in the publication and distribution of printed directories, including the PagesJaunes directory, L'Annuaire and online directories for the general public and businesses. It also provides Website creation, hosting, publication of the BtoB directories and publication of the QuiDonc reverse directory, complementary services such as the geographic services of Mappy and, in the field of direct marketing, the sale of data files and the processing of marketing databases by PagesJaunes Marketing Services. The Company publishes directories in Spain, Luxembourg, Belgium and Morocco. It operates through its various subsidiaries, including PagesJaunes SA, PagesJaunes Marketing Services, 123people, QDQ Media, Eur Directory and Mappy, among others. In February 2014, it created five new business units dedicated to Retail business, Services and Health & Public businesses, Home business, BtoB business and Solocal Network.

docs.name: Scientific Brain Training SA (MLSBT)
docs.description: Scientific Brain Training SBT SA is a France-based company that specializes in cognitive engineering and develops products to test the users in the areas of cognitive psychology and neuropsychology. The tests are done through Internet and mobile phone technology, as well as printed materials, among others. SBT is principally engaged in two distinct market sectors: Human Resources and Preventive Healthcare. In the Human Resources sector, the Company develops activities for evaluating the cognitive potential of individuals for companies and specialist agencies. In the Preventive Healthcare sector, SBT provides cognitive stimulation tools for medical practitioners such as psychologists and neurologists, or insurance-type organizations, retirement funds and pharmaceutical laboratories. SBT also provides products for mature adults who want to maintain their mental capabilities, as well as tools to enable children to develop their cognitive skills.

docs.name: Philippine Stock Index: Holding Firms
docs.description: The PSE index series consists of the PSEi, six sector indices and the All Shares Index. The base level of the PSEi was pegged at 1,022.045 points. This was reckoned according to the close of the index on February 28, 1990, which is the PSEi base date. With the exception of the All Shares Index, all these indices are free float-adjusted. The PSE Index Series is calculated in Philippine Pesos (Php). The PSEi is the main index of the Exchange. It is composed of a fixed basket of 30 companies, whose selection is based on a specific set of criteria. The PSE also maintains six sector indices representing each major sector under the revised industry classification of the Exchange. These indices are the (1) Financials Index; (2) Industrial Index; (3) Holding Firms Index; (4) Property Index; (5) Services Index; and (6) Mining & Oil Index. More info at http://www.pse.com.ph/resource/filetemplate/file/pseindexguide.pdf.
